<item>
            <title>[NET-262] SubnetUtils does not handle /31 and /32 CIDRs well</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NET-262</link>
                <project id="12310487" key="NET">Commons Net</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;SubnetUtils does not handle /31 and /32 CIDRs well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This should be documented and/or fixed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;192.168.0.1/32 causes an IllegalArgumentException to be thrown (by the way, that should show the upper and lower bounds)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;192.168.0.3/31 gives &lt;br/&gt;
addressCount=0, &lt;br/&gt;
low =192.168.0.3 &lt;br/&gt;
high=192.168.0.2&lt;br/&gt;
and 192.168.0.3 is rejected as not in range&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
